"{\"uid\": \"forbes.com-sites-micheleherrmann-2024-08-09-this-french-low-cost-airline-is-buzzing-amid-the-2024-summer-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"ByMichele Herrmann,  Contributor.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 33, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Amid the 2024 Summer Olympics, it's been a busy season for airlines flying to and from Paris along with Tahiti.\", \"from\": 35, \"to\": 146, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 122, \"end\": 127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3274242390498594e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 139, \"end\": 145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9600286550175195, \"rank\": 0.0416355749106751, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among them,French beehas been making their place in sky with service not only to the City of Lights but also the French Polynesian capital of Papeete.\", \"from\": 147, \"to\": 297, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 158, \"end\": 164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9997555889149166, \"rank\": 0.0001692480704120459, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 260, \"end\": 266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9997555889149166, \"rank\": 0.0001692480704120459, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 267, \"end\": 277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.9978657758940419, \"rank\": 0.0011041574430586199, \"text\": \"Polynesian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\"}, {\"begin\": 289, \"end\": 296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Papeete\", \"score\": 0.9999999989072421, \"rank\": 1.0929044169330985e-09, \"text\": \"Papeete\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Papeete\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Papeete\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Also with this low-cost carrier, August marks the one-year anniversary of the appointment of current CEO and President Christine Ourmi\\u00e8res-Widener.\", \"from\": 299, \"to\": 446, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 418, \"end\": 427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christine_Blair\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.3887769067008915e-12, \"text\": \"Christine\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christine_Blair\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christine_Blair\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ourmi\\u00e8res-Widener is French bee's first female CEO, guiding this eight-year-old nonstop carrier from certain U.S. routes to Paris Orly, its home airport.\", \"from\": 448, \"to\": 601, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 469, \"end\": 479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French bee\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\"}, {\"begin\": 557, \"end\": 561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997957377914765, \"rank\": 0.00011107583091430617, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 572, \"end\": 582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orly_Airport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Orly\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orly_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orly_Airport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With an engineering degree from Isae-ENSMA and master's degree in marketing from ESSEC Business School, the Avignon native has established a designated route for herself within the aviation industry.\", \"from\": 603, \"to\": 802, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 684, \"end\": 705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ESSEC_Business_School\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"ESSEC Business School\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ESSEC_Business_School\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ESSEC_Business_School\"}, {\"begin\": 711, \"end\": 718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Avignon\", \"score\": 0.997578276307981, \"rank\": 0.0024276026751257275, \"text\": \"Avignon\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Avignon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Avignon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Upon graduating from school, Ourmi\\u00e8res-Widener was recruited by Air France and started out by fixing aircraft such as airbuses and the famous Concorde in a maintenance hangar.\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 979, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 868, \"end\": 878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Air_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2277760625371624e-77, \"text\": \"Air France\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Air_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Air_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was the only woman surrounded by very experienced technicians,\\\" she remembered.\", \"from\": 980, \"to\": 1062, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Overtime, Ourmi\\u00e8res-Widener would advance within Air France through various positions from the late 1990s through 2010 and onward.\", \"from\": 1064, \"to\": 1194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1113, \"end\": 1123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Air_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2277760625371624e-77, \"text\": \"Air France\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Air_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Air_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For one year, she was the first woman to lead Air France-KLM in the United States (2009-2010).\", \"from\": 1195, \"to\": 1289, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1241, \"end\": 1255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Air_France\\u2013KLM\", \"score\": 0.9999965368907335, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Air France-KLM\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Air_France\\u2013KLM\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Air_France\\u2013KLM\"}, {\"begin\": 1263, \"end\": 1276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999871717650154, \"rank\": 1.2828399229031227e-05, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In her final role with France's flag carrier, she oversaw 14 airports with a turnover of $1.6 billion.\", \"from\": 1290, \"to\": 1392, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1313, \"end\": 1319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.076057341983557e-14, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ourmi\\u00e8res-Widener's resume also lists years at Amadeus, a French travel technology company, and as global sales director at American Express Global Business Travel.\", \"from\": 1394, \"to\": 1558, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1452, \"end\": 1458, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9997555889149166, \"rank\": 0.0001692480704120459, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1518, \"end\": 1557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Express\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5196690059874842e-28, \"text\": \"American Express Global Business Travel\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Express\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Express\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her past leadership roles range from CEO and COO of CityJet, an Irish regional airline, to CEO of Flybe, a British low-cost carrier, until July 2019.\", \"from\": 1560, \"to\": 1709, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1605, \"end\": 1608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chief_operating_officer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5386801639590256e-32, \"text\": \"COO\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chief_operating_officer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chief_operating_officer\"}, {\"begin\": 1612, \"end\": 1619, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CityJet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"CityJet\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CityJet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CityJet\"}, {\"begin\": 1624, \"end\": 1629, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.7222663448719069, \"rank\": 0.38448329559360844, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 1658, \"end\": 1663, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flybe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5724828184084232e-56, \"text\": \"Flybe\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flybe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flybe\"}, {\"begin\": 1667, \"end\": 1674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999998747048345, \"rank\": 1.2472226021296503e-07, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Also that year, she sold the latter airline to an investment consortium.\", \"from\": 1710, \"to\": 1782, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Right before French bee, Ourmi\\u00e8res-Widener led TAP Air Portugal, where her two-year tenure resulted in turning around the low-cost Portuguese airline by achieving record profitability in 2022 amid spearheading a complex restructuring plan.\", \"from\": 1784, \"to\": 2023, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1797, \"end\": 1807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French bee\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\"}, {\"begin\": 1831, \"end\": 1847, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TAP_Air_Portugal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"TAP Air Portugal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TAP_Air_Portugal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TAP_Air_Portugal\"}, {\"begin\": 1915, \"end\": 1925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portugal\", \"score\": 0.9496959447104386, \"rank\": 0.05068082459017134, \"text\": \"Portuguese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portugal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portugal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Regardless of her role, Ourmi\\u00e8res-Widener always recognizes behind the magic behind a plane takeoff or landing, in how an extensive network of aviation workers make it all possible.\", \"from\": 2025, \"to\": 2206, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There was something special about it,\\\" explained Ourmi\\u00e8res-Widener.\", \"from\": 2208, \"to\": 2276, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"And when I started my career, it was a confirmation; that was definitely a passion.\\\"\", \"from\": 2277, \"to\": 2362, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"French bee was launched in 2016, jointly by its first CEO and airline executive Marc Rochet, and Jean-Paul Dubreuil, chairman of its parent owner, Groupe Dubreuil.\", \"from\": 2364, \"to\": 2527, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2364, \"end\": 2374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French bee\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Initially known as \\\"French Blue,\\\" the airline's name was rebranded to French bee to avoid a potential lawsuit with JetBlue.\", \"from\": 2529, \"to\": 2652, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2549, \"end\": 2560, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.220263910134218e-27, \"text\": \"French Blue\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\"}, {\"begin\": 2599, \"end\": 2609, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French bee\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\"}, {\"begin\": 2644, \"end\": 2651, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JetBlue\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"JetBlue\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JetBlue\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JetBlue\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the summer of 2017, the company added R\\u00e9union Island, then San Francisco and Tahiti in 2018 to its flight schedule, and then to New York via Newark in 2021.\", \"from\": 2653, \"to\": 2812, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2715, \"end\": 2728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco_International_Airport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.236277069623342e-22, \"text\": \"San Francisco\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco_International_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco_International_Airport\"}, {\"begin\": 2733, \"end\": 2739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9600286550175195, \"rank\": 0.0416355749106751, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}, {\"begin\": 2784, \"end\": 2792, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999950392857762, \"rank\": 4.955504525912635e-06, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}, {\"begin\": 2797, \"end\": 2803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newark_Liberty_International_Airport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.331283490837381e-36, \"text\": \"Newark\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newark_Liberty_International_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newark_Liberty_International_Airport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their U.S. flight nonstop routes to Orly also include Miami and Los Angeles, along with a San Francisco flight to Papeete.\", \"from\": 2813, \"to\": 2935, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2867, \"end\": 2872, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miami_International_Airport\", \"score\": 0.9999999994624886, \"rank\": 5.373205766398217e-10, \"text\": \"Miami\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miami_International_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Miami_International_Airport\"}, {\"begin\": 2877, \"end\": 2888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_International_Airport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.337925023302978e-15, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_International_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_International_Airport\"}, {\"begin\": 2903, \"end\": 2916, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco_International_Airport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.236277069623342e-22, \"text\": \"San Francisco\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco_International_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco_International_Airport\"}, {\"begin\": 2927, \"end\": 2934, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Papeete\", \"score\": 0.9999999989072421, \"rank\": 1.0929044169330985e-09, \"text\": \"Papeete\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Papeete\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Papeete\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As French bee's CEO, Ourmi\\u00e8res-Widener joins a group of other female aviation CEOs such as Aer Lingus' Lynne Embleton, Japan Airlines' Tottori Mitsuko and JetBlue's Joanna Geraghty.\", \"from\": 2937, \"to\": 3118, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2940, \"end\": 2950, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French bee\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\"}, {\"begin\": 3028, \"end\": 3038, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aer_Lingus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.59558450204687e-72, \"text\": \"Aer Lingus\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aer_Lingus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aer_Lingus\"}, {\"begin\": 3046, \"end\": 3054, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Embleton,_Northumberland\", \"score\": 0.7563603882089137, \"rank\": 0.16719883889698328, \"text\": \"Embleton\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Embleton,_Northumberland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Embleton,_Northumberland\"}, {\"begin\": 3056, \"end\": 3070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_Airlines\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Japan Airlines\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_Airlines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_Airlines\"}, {\"begin\": 3092, \"end\": 3099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JetBlue\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"JetBlue\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JetBlue\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JetBlue\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a good sign following a 2021 survey by theInternational Air Transport Associationon how women are still under-represented in leadership roles with airlines.\", \"from\": 3120, \"to\": 3281, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In response to a pilot shortage, there is now a push to fill this employment gap by giving more opportunities to women.\", \"from\": 3282, \"to\": 3401, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think it's wonderful to see that how has it been for females working in the aviation industry,\\\" said Ourmi\\u00e8res-Widener.\", \"from\": 3403, \"to\": 3525, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With bookings, French bee offers three fare categories - Basic, Smart and Premium.\", \"from\": 3527, \"to\": 3609, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3542, \"end\": 3552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French bee\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Across them, passengers can include add-ons like amenity kits and various seating assignments.\", \"from\": 3610, \"to\": 3704, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A unique French bee booking option is the Train + Air service, a package combining these two travel methods.\", \"from\": 3706, \"to\": 3814, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3715, \"end\": 3725, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French bee\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Done in partnership with SNCF (French Railways), the package services 15 train stations, including Aix-en-Provence TGV, Avignon TGV, Lyon Part-Dieu and Marseille St-Charles.\", \"from\": 3815, \"to\": 3988, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3930, \"end\": 3933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TGV\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"TGV\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TGV\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TGV\"}, {\"begin\": 3967, \"end\": 3976, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille_Provence_Airport\", \"score\": 0.9999993932894562, \"rank\": 6.067110680882139e-07, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille_Provence_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille_Provence_Airport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Citing the push in France to switch from the use of domestic flights to more in-country rail travel, Ourmi\\u00e8res-Widener thinks that promoting the connection from Orly shows how beneficial this method of travel is.\", \"from\": 3990, \"to\": 4202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4009, \"end\": 4015, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.076057341983557e-14, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We also do a lot online because our customers want to do everything online,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 4204, \"to\": 4291, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have a helpdesk that is also based within the U.S. for U.S.\", \"from\": 4292, \"to\": 4355, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4351, \"end\": 4355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997957377914765, \"rank\": 0.00011107583091430617, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"customers.\\\"\", \"from\": 4356, \"to\": 4367, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In preparing for the 2024 Olympics, Ourmi\\u00e8res-Widener noted that French bee held coordination planning meetings on logistics for Paris and France's overseas collectivities.\", \"from\": 4369, \"to\": 4541, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4434, \"end\": 4444, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French bee\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Bee\"}, {\"begin\": 4498, \"end\": 4503, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3274242390498594e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org